''AKA VNI''

[[VNI|VXLAN Network Identifier]] is similar to [[VLAN ID]], but it's 24-bit (while [[VID|VLAN ID]] is only 12-bit), so it allows for many more [[VXLANs|Virtual Extensible LAN]] than [[VLANs|VLAN]].

